My husband has dubbed these "Orgasmic Ribs". Of course I did things a little bit differently but the wine/mustard combo is what makes this recipe. I only used a 750ml bottle (merlot) wine which was about 3 cups not 4. I simmered it down to 1 cup and added the mustard as the recipe stated. Instead of all those shallots I used only 4 shallots but added 4 cloves garlic and 2 coursely chopped onions. Be sure to trim as much fat from the ribs as you can before browning them. I had about 4 lbs ribs. I sprinkled them with some seasoned salt before browning. Then I put everything in a preheated crockpot (!) and let it cook on high for about four hours. Every hour I moved the ribs around a little because the crockpot was crowded. After 4 hours I switched to low and added a large can of tomatoes (tomatoes drained and cut in half) and simmered for another 2 hours. I also added some baby carrots at that point. I served it with mashed potatoes. There was so much delicious gravy at the end because of doing it in the crockpot. The next day was even better. The fat in the leftover gravy rose to the top and was easy to remove. The flavor was incredible; my husband's eyes were rolling in joy!

